          ETrafficLightColor assessment
          The assessment color of the finding (may be null).

        • siblingLocations

          java.util.List<E> siblingLocations
          The locations of other findings that are considered siblings. This is, e.g., used to find other clone instances in the same clone class. As this is commonly empty, we keep this attribute null in this case to save space for serialization. The access methods, however, handle this transparently.

        • secondaryLocations

          java.util.List<E> secondaryLocations
          Next to the primary location DetachedFinding.location, a finding may optionally have secondary locations. For instance, an architecture finding may contain the individual source code locations of the violating identifiers.

        • properties

          java.util.Map<K,V> properties
          Properties for this finding. Each finding can be associated with one or more properties describing details of the finding (e.g. length of long method, etc.). These properties are also displayed in the UI and can be used for sorting findings (in which case the value class must be comparable).

        • statementPath

          java.util.List<E> statementPath
          See Also:
          DetachedFinding.getStatementPath()

          java.lang.String deepestRelativePathWithMoreThanOneChild
          Contains the relative uniform path of the deepest child container which has more than one child while all its parent containers (up to this one) have exactly one child. If this has more than one child or no children, this holds the empty string.

        • children

          The children as a map from their uniform path to the content hash. In the case of a container, this prefix is followed by the ContainerInfo.deepestRelativePathWithMoreThanOneChild value of the child element.

          The uniform path of the test (method) that was executed. This is an absolute (i.e. hierarchical) reference which identifies the test uniquely in the scope of the Teamscale project.           The uniform path the test (unescaped and without -test- prefix).

        • sourcePath

          java.lang.String sourcePath
          Path to the source of the method. Will be equal to TestDetails.uniformPath in most cases, but e.g. @Test methods in a base class will have the sourcePath pointing to the base class which contains the actual implementation, whereas TestDetails.uniformPath will contain the class name of the most specific subclass from where it was actually executed.

        • content

          java.lang.String content
          Some kind of content to tell whether the test specification has changed. Can be revision number or hash over the specification or similar.

        • lastChangedTimestamp

          long lastChangedTimestamp
          The last timestamp at which the content of the test did change.
